abstract: Novartis AG has secured Medicaid coverage for a pricey new sickle cell disease therapy in two U.S. states just weeks after winning U.S. approval, following an early campaign to convince local officials of its value, according to a company executive and a Reuters review of public filings.
snippet: Novartis AG has secured Medicaid coverage for a pricey new sickle cell disease therapy in two U.S. states just weeks after winning U.S. approval, following an early campaign to convince local officials of its value, according to a company executiv...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Novartis AG has secured Medicaid coverage for a pricey new sickle cell disease therapy in two U.S. states just weeks after winning U.S. approval, following an early campaign to convince local officials of its value, according to a company executive and a Reuters review of public filings.
headline_main: Novartis Wins Medicaid Approval for New Sickle Cell Drug in Key U.S. States
headline_print_headline: Novartis Wins Medicaid Approval for New Sickle Cell Drug in Key U.S. States

abstract: The Irish High Court will rule on Monday Dec. 23 on whether Ryanair can prevent its operations chief Peter Bellew from joining arch-rival easyJet until 2021, a court official said on Friday.
snippet: The Irish High Court will rule on Monday Dec. 23 on whether Ryanair can prevent its operations chief Peter Bellew from joining arch-rival easyJet until 2021, a court official said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: DUBLIN — The Irish High Court will rule on Monday Dec. 23 on whether Ryanair can prevent its operations chief Peter Bellew from joining arch-rival easyJet until 2021, a court official said on Friday.
headline_main: Ruling on Ryanair Bid to Delay COO's easyJet Move Set for December 23
headline_print_headline: Ruling on Ryanair Bid to Delay COO's easyJet Move Set for December 23

abstract: Hungary's government has taken over six privately owned fertility clinics and boosted funding to make treatments accessible to many more couples in a bid to reverse a population decline, the government said.
snippet: Hungary's government has taken over six privately owned fertility clinics and boosted funding to make treatments accessible to many more couples in a bid to reverse a population decline, the government said.
lead_paragraph: BUDAPEST — Hungary's government has taken over six privately owned fertility clinics and boosted funding to make treatments accessible to many more couples in a bid to reverse a population decline, the government said.
headline_main: Hungarian Government Takes Over Fertility Clinics to Boost Birth Rate
headline_print_headline: Hungarian Government Takes Over Fertility Clinics to Boost Birth Rate

abstract: Americans increased their spending in November at the fastest pace in four months, and income growth rebounded to its strongest gain since August.
snippet: Americans increased their spending in November at the fastest pace in four months, and income growth rebounded to its strongest gain since August.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Americans increased their spending in November at the fastest pace in four months, and income growth rebounded to its strongest gain since August.
headline_main: US Consumer Spending Up 0.4% in November, Best Since July
headline_print_headline: US Consumer Spending Up 0.4% in November, Best Since July

abstract: Weeks after U.S. authorities brought a spying case against three Saudi nationals for digging up dissidents' personal data at Twitter, the company suspended tens of thousands of accounts that appear to be linked to one suspect's company.
snippet: Weeks after U.S. authorities brought a spying case against three Saudi nationals for digging up dissidents' personal data at Twitter, the company suspended tens of thousands of accounts that appear to be linked to one suspect's company.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Weeks after U.S. authorities brought a spying case against three Saudi nationals for digging up dissidents' personal data at Twitter, the company suspended tens of thousands of accounts that appear to be linked to one suspect's company.
headline_main: Twitter Suspends Accounts Linked to Saudi Spying Case
headline_print_headline: Twitter Suspends Accounts Linked to Saudi Spying Case

abstract: Pakistani Islamist militant Hafiz Saeed, the alleged mastermind of deadly 2008 attacks in Mumbai, pleaded not guilty on Friday in a second case on charges of financing terrorism, a government prosecutor and a defense lawyer said.
snippet: Pakistani Islamist militant Hafiz Saeed, the alleged mastermind of deadly 2008 attacks in Mumbai, pleaded not guilty on Friday in a second case on charges of financing terrorism, a government prosecutor and a defense lawyer said.
lead_paragraph: LAHORE, Pakistan — Pakistani Islamist militant Hafiz Saeed, the alleged mastermind of deadly 2008 attacks in Mumbai, pleaded not guilty on Friday in a second case on charges of financing terrorism, a government prosecutor and a defense lawyer said.
headline_main: Pakistani Islamist Leader Pleads Not Guilty on Terrorism Financing Charges
headline_print_headline: Pakistani Islamist Leader Pleads Not Guilty on Terrorism Financing Charges

abstract: President Tayyip Erdogan said on Friday that Turkey will not stay silent over Russian-backed mercenaries supporting Khalifa Haftar in Libya, as Moscow voiced concerns over possible Turkish military deployment to Libya in support of Haftar's enemies.
snippet: President Tayyip Erdogan said on Friday that Turkey will not stay silent over Russian-backed mercenaries supporting Khalifa Haftar in Libya, as Moscow voiced concerns over possible Turkish military deployment to Libya in support of Haftar's enemie...
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW/ANKARA — President Tayyip Erdogan said on Friday that Turkey will not stay silent over Russian-backed mercenaries supporting Khalifa Haftar in Libya, as Moscow voiced concerns over possible Turkish military deployment to Libya in support of Haftar's enemies.
headline_main: Erdogan Says Turkey Won't Be Silent Over Mercenaries in Libya
headline_print_headline: Erdogan Says Turkey Won't Be Silent Over Mercenaries in Libya

abstract: Lebanon's new prime minister designate Hassan Diab said in an interview with Deutsche Welle he will work on forming a government within six weeks to help pull the country out of a deepening economic and political crisis.
snippet: Lebanon's new prime minister designate Hassan Diab said in an interview with Deutsche Welle he will work on forming a government within six weeks to help pull the country out of a deepening economic and political crisis.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Lebanon's new prime minister designate Hassan Diab said in an interview with Deutsche Welle he will work on forming a government within six weeks to help pull the country out of a deepening economic and political crisis.
headline_main: Lebanon's New PM Aims to Form Government Within Six Weeks: Deutsche Welle Interview
headline_print_headline: Lebanon's New PM Aims to Form Government Within Six Weeks: Deutsche Welle Interview

abstract: Poland's lower house of parliament approved the latest reform of the judiciary on Friday, despite the European Commission calling it to hold off adopting a law which it says would imperil the rule of law.
snippet: Poland's lower house of parliament approved the latest reform of the judiciary on Friday, despite the European Commission calling it to hold off adopting a law which it says would imperil the rule of law.
lead_paragraph: WARSAW/BRUSSELS — Poland's lower house of parliament approved the latest reform of the judiciary on Friday, despite the European Commission calling it to hold off adopting a law which it says would imperil the rule of law.
headline_main: Poland Lower House Adopts Judiciary Reform Despite EU Concerns
headline_print_headline: Poland Lower House Adopts Judiciary Reform Despite EU Concerns

abstract: The accusations included seven murder conspiracies, as well as gun running and drug trafficking.
snippet: The accusations included seven murder conspiracies, as well as gun running and drug trafficking.
lead_paragraph: Over the course of 150 pages, the indictment described a remarkably vast criminal enterprise. There were seven murder plots with guns, machetes and Molotov cocktails. There were assaults in bars, meetings in local bakeries and gang initiations with 13-second beatings.
